# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .graphifyignore — reduce structural/scaffolding noise in the Graphify graph.
#
# Goal: keep DOMAIN signal (source code, services, controllers, entities,
# shared libs, architecture docs, runtime/infra topology) and drop the Nx/TS
# CONFIG scaffolding that explodes into hundreds of near-duplicate
# `compilerOptions` / `dependencies` / target-config nodes.
#
# Semantics: gitignore rules, merged AFTER .gitignore (last-match-wins, `!`
# negations supported). This can only ever exclude MORE than .gitignore.
# node_modules/, dist/, coverage/, tmp/, out-tsc/ and .nx/cache are already
# excluded by .gitignore.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Graph + tool outputs — never graph the graph itself
graphify-out/
.nx/

# ── TypeScript project/config files ──────────────────────────────────────────
# 1 tsconfig per project × 4 variants (base/app/lib/spec) → the single biggest
# noise source (every `compilerOptions` flag becomes a node). Pure build config;
# no domain/architecture signal.
tsconfig.json
tsconfig.*.json
**/tsconfig.json
**/tsconfig.*.json

# ── Nx workspace config ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Plugins/targets/namedInputs → config-only, regenerable, high node count.
nx.json

# ── Package manifests & lockfiles ────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOTE (partial-exclusion decision): today every service's package.json holds
# IDENTICAL framework deps (@nestjs/*, rxjs, tslib) and inlined Nx targets —
# pure noise, zero cross-service boundary signal (services talk via gRPC/RabbitMQ
# and share @orbit/* libs, not via package.json deps). So they are excluded.
# RE-INCLUDE per-service manifests once a service actually declares real
# `@orbit/*` dependencies (then package.json encodes true service→lib boundaries):
#   e.g. add below:  !apps/*/package.json   and   !libs/*/package.json
package.json
**/package.json
package-lock.json
**/package-lock.json

# project.json — none today (TS-solution inlines Nx config in package.json);
# kept here so a future switch to project.json stays noise-free by default.
**/project.json

# ── Lint / test / build / bundler config ─────────────────────────────────────
eslint.config.mjs
**/eslint.config.mjs
jest.config.ts
jest.preset.js
**/jest.config.ts
**/jest.config.cts
**/webpack.config.js
**/next.config.js
**/postcss.config.js
**/.swcrc
**/.spec.swcrc

# Generated TS shims (Next.js) — not authored, no signal
**/next-env.d.ts
**/index.d.ts

# ── Editor / formatter / agent-harness config ────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.prettierrc
.prettierignore
.editorconfig
.claude/settings.json
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/worktrees/
# .claude/skills/ IS graphed — the orbit-* build playbooks are domain knowledge, not config noise

# ── Nx template tooling docs (create-nx-workspace scaffolding, NOT Orbit domain)
# These generated skill/agent/prompt docs created the CI-monitor / nx-import /
# nx-generate communities and a large share of dangling semantic edges.
# NOTE: .github/workflows/ci.yml is deliberately KEPT (real CI/deploy signal).
.github/skills/
.github/agents/
.github/prompts/
